<p>We can <strong>read / write</strong> data in <strong>memory</strong> like this :   </p>  <pre><code>static void Main(string[] args) {     using (var ms = new MemoryStream())     {         var sw = new StreamWriter(ms);         sw.WriteLine("Hello World");         sw.Flush();         ms.Position = 0;         var sr = new StreamReader(ms);         var myStr = sr.ReadToEnd();         Console.WriteLine(myStr);     }      Console.WriteLine("Press any key to continue.");     Console.ReadKey(); } </code></pre>  <p>Now i want to write data on Ram (Memory = Random Access Memory) and read those data from <strong>Another Applicatio</strong>n?<br> How can i do that and <strong>Share</strong> a string in memory?   </p>  <p><strong>Important Note :</strong> I don't want to write any data on hard disk.<br> <strong>Edit :</strong> My .net version is 3.5</p>